WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:18.594 --> 00:00:22.271
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
... <font color="#138CE9">www.Addic7ed.com</font> ...

3
00:00:30.527 --> 00:00:34.116
What's the truth? What's true?

4
00:00:43.317 --> 00:00:45.901
I think we each have our own truth.

5
00:00:45.903 --> 00:00:47.446
So let me get this straight.

6
00:00:48.530 --> 00:00:49.531
Okay.

7
00:00:51.617 --> 00:00:53.366
You don't know why you're here.

8
00:00:53.368 --> 00:00:55.243
You don't know how I'm supposed to feel.

9
00:00:55.245 --> 00:00:56.995
You don't know why I haven't seen you

10
00:00:56.997 --> 00:00:59.456
and have tried not to
think about you for months

11
00:00:59.458 --> 00:01:01.752
and then you show up tonight.

12
00:01:02.836 --> 00:01:04.920
Precise and accurate.

13
00:01:04.922 --> 00:01:06.880
in true Clay Jensen style.

14
00:01:06.882 --> 00:01:08.743
You're still allowed to make fun of me.

15
00:01:08.746 --> 00:01:11.454
Allowed? Obligated? Who can say?

16
00:01:12.304 --> 00:01:13.805
Are you real?

17
00:01:13.808 --> 00:01:15.263
Do you see me?

18
00:01:15.265 --> 00:01:16.473
Are you corporeal?

19
00:01:16.475 --> 00:01:18.683
That seems like a
science-fiction question.

20
00:01:18.685 --> 00:01:21.021
- Can I touch you?
- That seems like a loaded question.

21
00:01:23.982 --> 00:01:26.985
This is fucked up. right?
Like. I'm seriously fucked up.

22
00:01:27.653 --> 00:01:31.823
I don't think you're fucked up.
You're just... working through things.

23
00:01:32.950 --> 00:01:36.119
- Things like seeing a ghost?
- And other things.

24
00:01:38.277 --> 00:01:39.602
So you are a ghost.

25
00:01:40.581 --> 00:01:43.332
Okay. does it matter what
you call me? I'm here.

26
00:01:43.335 --> 00:01:46.266
- And you're here for a reason?
- I would think so.

27
00:01:47.339 --> 00:01:50.425
- But you don't know what it is.
- I was hoping you would.

28
00:01:51.218 --> 00:01:53.677
- And you're not going away.
- I don't think so.

29
00:01:53.679 --> 00:01:54.888
I mean. not for the moment.

30
00:02:01.061 --> 00:02:02.521
Well. that's just fucking great.

31
00:02:09.152 --> 00:02:11.444
Clay!

32
00:02:11.446 --> 00:02:12.904
Clay!

33
00:02:12.906 --> 00:02:14.116
You're going to be late.

34
00:02:16.406 --> 00:02:17.633
Shit.

35
00:02:18.745 --> 00:02:20.662
Clay?

36
00:02:20.664 --> 00:02:21.832
Are you all right?

37
00:02:23.750 --> 00:02:26.253
Uh. sorry! I'm fine.
I'm fine. I overslept.

38
00:02:30.382 --> 00:02:34.801
- You slept in your clothes?
- Yeah. Homework and stuff.

39
00:02:34.804 --> 00:02:38.641
- But. um. everything's okay?
- Yeah. all good.

40
00:02:40.976 --> 00:02:42.477
How was court yesterday?

41
00:02:44.813 --> 00:02:46.271
Why don't you tell me?

42
00:02:46.273 --> 00:02:50.693
I was just there to drop off
some files. How about you?

43
00:02:50.696 --> 00:02:52.232
I was just curious.

44
00:02:53.155 --> 00:02:55.780
Clay. I know you said you
don't think about Hannah.

45
00:02:55.782 --> 00:02:58.919
that you don't care about her anymore.

46
00:02:58.922 --> 00:03:01.318
but I am worried that that's not true.

47
00:03:03.623 --> 00:03:04.783
Gotta get dressed for school.

48
00:03:06.055 --> 00:03:07.708
Well...

49
00:03:07.711 --> 00:03:09.878
- Okay.
- Okay.

50
00:03:09.880 --> 00:03:11.005
Bye.

51
00:03:12.716 --> 00:03:16.178
- Nothing's going on?
- I have to go to school.

52
00:03:17.012 --> 00:03:20.430
- And you don't care about me anymore?
- Look. I tried. Hannah.

53
00:03:20.432 --> 00:03:22.934
I did everything I could
for you. and nothing worked.

54
00:03:23.560 --> 00:03:24.841
Nothing.

55
00:03:24.844 --> 00:03:28.065
And now you're back? And
there's still nothing I can do.

56
00:03:28.857 --> 00:03:30.817
If that's true. why am I here?

57
00:03:32.569 --> 00:03:34.071
Yeah. Exactly.

58
00:03:39.427 --> 00:03:40.619
What the hell?

59
00:03:46.667 --> 00:03:48.085
Shit. I gotta go.

60
00:04:04.810 --> 00:04:08.355
"Hannah wasn't the only one."
What do you suppose that means?

61
00:04:12.956 --> 00:04:14.236
Who gave it to you?

62
00:04:15.112 --> 00:04:17.614
And why now. the day my trial started?

63
00:04:20.701 --> 00:04:24.035
- You think they're connected?
- You think they're not?

64
00:04:27.957 --> 00:04:32.042
I think that I need to get
dressed. and go to school.

65
00:04:32.045 --> 00:04:33.502
and try to live my life.

66
00:04:52.858 --> 00:04:54.025
Saddle up. partner.

67
00:04:56.652 --> 00:04:58.736
Did we talk about you giving me a ride?

68
00:04:58.739 --> 00:04:59.865
Did we have to?

69
00:05:01.284 --> 00:05:02.617
I mean. no. but. um...

70
00:05:04.064 --> 00:05:05.689
Should we talk about last night?

71
00:05:05.692 --> 00:05:08.588
How about instead of
talking. we just ride?

72
00:05:16.882 --> 00:05:19.081
We all have things we keep hidden.

73
00:05:20.509 --> 00:05:23.635
Sometimes. keeping secrets
is how you survive.

74
00:05:32.272 --> 00:05:33.938
Because in high school.

75
00:05:33.940 --> 00:05:36.956
- one rumor. one picture...
- Yes.

76
00:05:36.959 --> 00:05:40.190
One incident. can define you forever.

77
00:05:45.327 --> 00:05:46.912
You're doing the right thing. honey.

78
00:05:48.401 --> 00:05:49.659
I know.

79
00:05:50.404 --> 00:05:54.625
Now it's gonna be out there.
Everything I said in my deposition.

80
00:05:54.628 --> 00:05:56.748
Look. what happened to
Hannah after that photo.

81
00:05:56.749 --> 00:05:58.713
it happened to you. too.

82
00:05:58.715 --> 00:06:00.089
And that is not your fault.

83
00:06:00.091 --> 00:06:04.424
You told the truth. And that's
all you're gonna do again today.

84
00:06:08.600 --> 00:06:10.268
- Is that Mikey?
- Uh...

85
00:06:11.144 --> 00:06:12.894
Aww. Todd. look.

86
00:06:12.897 --> 00:06:16.573
Wow. Wow. he is a keeper. huh?

87
00:06:17.108 --> 00:06:18.235
I guess he is.

88
00:06:19.528 --> 00:06:21.530
And the truth doesn't even matter.

89
00:06:23.182 --> 00:06:24.906
Barry e-mailed me last night.

90
00:06:24.908 --> 00:06:27.992
He said it was Bryce's idea.
that Bryce asked you yesterday.

91
00:06:27.994 --> 00:06:29.410
Asked me what?

92
00:06:29.412 --> 00:06:31.010
If we want to use their lawyer.

93
00:06:31.013 --> 00:06:34.581
I'm not gonna let you take the
stand without some guidance.

94
00:06:34.584 --> 00:06:38.294
This kind of thing can ruin somebody's
life. even if they're innocent.

95
00:06:38.296 --> 00:06:41.256
I know. it's just... We can
find our own lawyer. It's fine.

96
00:06:41.258 --> 00:06:43.925
This is the kind of thing
your father used to handle.

97
00:06:43.927 --> 00:06:47.806
At times like these. we need to
benefit from our associations.

98
00:06:51.851 --> 00:06:53.478
- Who is it?
- It's. uh...

99
00:06:54.354 --> 00:06:56.187
Bryce. actually.

100
00:06:56.189 --> 00:06:58.523
He probably wants to get some
throws in before practice.

101
00:06:58.525 --> 00:07:01.319
- I should go.
- Okay. honey. And tell him thanks.

102
00:07:03.363 --> 00:07:05.782
- No. I wanna testify.
- But...?

103
00:07:06.866 --> 00:07:08.410
It's just...

104
00:07:10.537 --> 00:07:12.998
Tyler Down. who testified yesterday.

105
00:07:13.707 --> 00:07:15.750
called out a couple kids.
and they weren't happy.

106
00:07:16.587 --> 00:07:17.711
That's all.

107
00:07:19.546 --> 00:07:23.550
Well. if anybody gives you any flack.
you tell me. and I'll handle it.

108
00:07:25.817 --> 00:07:26.970
Thanks. Dad.

109
00:07:29.848 --> 00:07:33.641
When rumors spread.
you can fight them or ignore them.

110
00:07:33.643 --> 00:07:35.478
but they never really go away.

111
00:07:36.688 --> 00:07:38.396
When you're the target.

112
00:07:38.398 --> 00:07:40.982
you do anything you can
to protect yourself.

113
00:07:47.330 --> 00:07:49.545
Jess! Hey! You wanna help?

114
00:07:49.548 --> 00:07:50.744
Babe.

115
00:07:52.787 --> 00:07:54.039
Where else you want 'em?

116
00:07:56.041 --> 00:08:00.084
You guys are ridiculous. but sweet.

117
00:08:00.086 --> 00:08:02.795
Babe. thank you for
helping me with this.

118
00:08:02.797 --> 00:08:03.970
Come here.

119
00:08:06.927 --> 00:08:08.261
Sometimes you hide.

120
00:08:09.679 --> 00:08:11.072
Sometimes you fight back.

121
00:08:14.893 --> 00:08:16.227
Anything you have to do.

122
00:08:19.275 --> 00:08:20.482
There you go.

123
00:08:22.692 --> 00:08:23.693
Thank you.

124
00:08:26.947 --> 00:08:28.907
Good for you. Let's go.

125
00:08:30.283 --> 00:08:31.824
Such a gentleman.

126
00:08:31.826 --> 00:08:33.952
This doesn't mean I'm
gonna put out or anything.

127
00:08:33.954 --> 00:08:35.954
What? Not even a handy?

128
00:08:35.956 --> 00:08:38.500
- Oh. my hand doesn't really work...
- All right.

129
00:08:42.045 --> 00:08:44.504
Hey. you know what? Let's
take the side entrance today.

130
00:08:44.506 --> 00:08:47.840
- But it's way further. and I get tired.
- I can carry you. Come on.

131
00:08:47.842 --> 00:08:49.698
Okay. you're not... Dude. you're not...

132
00:08:49.701 --> 00:08:52.389
The whole reason I called you
was to avoid another scene.

133
00:08:53.181 --> 00:08:56.081
Getting picked up by my dad in the
cop car was embarrassing enough.

134
00:09:00.021 --> 00:09:02.989
Because the
thing is. in high school.

135
00:09:02.992 --> 00:09:05.396
everyone's watching you. all the time.

136
00:09:07.747 --> 00:09:09.322
You have to be careful.

137
00:09:12.967 --> 00:09:15.966
_

138
00:09:20.310 --> 00:09:21.521
Get my note?

139
00:09:24.420 --> 00:09:27.713
About dropping by the office?
I was hoping that we could chat.

140
00:09:27.716 --> 00:09:31.052
- About what?
- About anything that you need.

141
00:09:31.720 --> 00:09:35.054
Anything I can do to help
with what you're going through.

142
00:09:35.056 --> 00:09:38.599
Really? You think you can
be helpful all of a sudden?

143
00:09:40.186 --> 00:09:41.855
Yes. uh. I think I can.

144
00:09:43.231 --> 00:09:45.290
Look. I know what you think about me.

145
00:09:45.291 --> 00:09:47.558
you know. and about what happened.

146
00:09:48.827 --> 00:09:51.677
but the most important thing
to me right now. Jessica.

147
00:09:51.680 --> 00:09:53.116
is about keeping you safe.

148
00:09:55.326 --> 00:09:56.701
Jessica!

149
00:09:56.703 --> 00:09:58.997
Hey. where you been? We
still gotta celebrate. girl.

150
00:10:00.165 --> 00:10:02.500
Uh. the squad made
Jess a flyer yesterday.

151
00:10:03.501 --> 00:10:06.504
- Wow. congratulations. Ms. Davis.
- Thank you.

152
00:10:07.464 --> 00:10:09.466
- Think about what I said. okay?
- Yeah.

153
00:10:12.260 --> 00:10:14.471
Asshole. You're welcome.

154
00:10:15.427 --> 00:10:16.786
Do I know you?

155
00:10:16.789 --> 00:10:18.347
Uh...

156
00:10:18.349 --> 00:10:21.642
Nina Jones. And trust
me. Porter's clueless.

157
00:10:21.644 --> 00:10:23.772
It's better to keep your
mouth shut around him.

158
00:10:29.235 --> 00:10:32.278
You have to protect
yourself any way you can.

159
00:10:32.281 --> 00:10:33.518
So that's what I did.

160
00:10:34.491 --> 00:10:37.452
- What's going on? Who are these people?
- They're all here for you.

161
00:10:38.620 --> 00:10:40.330
My e-mail list of concerned moms has

162
00:10:40.333 --> 00:10:42.622
over a thousand names in this county.

163
00:10:42.624 --> 00:10:44.626
And moms do love a good craft project.

164
00:10:48.046 --> 00:10:50.924
That's... That's her school picture.

165
00:10:51.841 --> 00:10:53.426
Doesn't she look lovely?

166
00:10:54.636 --> 00:10:56.346
We're putting a face on this trial.

167
00:11:04.104 --> 00:11:06.110
She told me that her foundation wanted

168
00:11:06.113 --> 00:11:08.064
to provide whatever support I needed.

169
00:11:08.066 --> 00:11:11.859
- But she didn't specify a picket line.
- No.

170
00:11:11.861 --> 00:11:13.822
You have to be careful. okay?

171
00:11:15.031 --> 00:11:16.654
These pyrotechnics can be useful.

172
00:11:16.655 --> 00:11:19.077
but don't forget this
is still your show.

173
00:11:20.578 --> 00:11:22.705
- I know that.
- And she's staying with you?

174
00:11:23.665 --> 00:11:24.958
Well. I have a spare room.

175
00:11:25.875 --> 00:11:27.875
Dennis. the house is empty. It is...

176
00:11:27.877 --> 00:11:30.213
There's no reason for her
to pay for a hotel room.

177
00:11:31.005 --> 00:11:33.424
Just... be careful.

178
00:11:35.426 --> 00:11:39.095
I spread a rumor about
Hannah and I'm not proud of it.

179
00:11:39.097 --> 00:11:41.933
And what happened
after you spread that rumor?

180
00:11:43.226 --> 00:11:45.436
Boys asked me and Hannah
to have sex with them.

181
00:11:46.312 --> 00:11:50.064
Or got physical. And
they were aggressive.

182
00:11:50.066 --> 00:11:51.860
And I couldn't handle it.

183
00:11:53.236 --> 00:11:57.071
This was just a meaningless kiss.
All right? Girls do it all the time.

184
00:11:57.073 --> 00:12:00.743
And what to your direct
knowledge did the school do

185
00:12:01.536 --> 00:12:04.036
in response to Hannah
being sexually harassed?

186
00:12:04.038 --> 00:12:07.164
Or the fact that a lewd
photo of two students

187
00:12:07.166 --> 00:12:09.002
was being shared on campus?

188
00:12:10.501 --> 00:12:11.881
Nothing.

189
00:12:12.964 --> 00:12:14.215
The school did nothing.

190
00:12:18.720 --> 00:12:19.991
Who did this?

191
00:12:22.181 --> 00:12:24.434
Someone I talked about
yesterday. I'm guessing.

192
00:12:27.037 --> 00:12:28.451
At the trial.

193
00:12:32.108 --> 00:12:34.068
This is what happens
when you tell the truth.

194
00:12:39.498 --> 00:12:40.771
Ask him.

195
00:12:42.367 --> 00:12:44.283
Did you just come here

196
00:12:44.284 --> 00:12:46.703
to look at the destruction
that is my life. or...?

197
00:12:46.706 --> 00:12:48.499
No. I was wondering. do you ever...

198
00:12:49.876 --> 00:12:51.169
work with Polaroids?

199
00:12:52.712 --> 00:12:54.213
Amateur hipster tripe.

200
00:12:55.715 --> 00:13:00.009
- I'll take that as a no.
- It's retro analog bullshit.

201
00:13:00.011 --> 00:13:03.638
- There's no negatives. what's the point?
- Unless that is the point.

202
00:13:03.640 --> 00:13:05.556
So no one can make a copy?

203
00:13:05.558 --> 00:13:07.340
No. you can make a copy of anything.

204
00:13:07.341 --> 00:13:08.895
you just take a digital picture of it.

205
00:13:10.480 --> 00:13:13.524
But. yeah. you want one print
to hold on to. take a Polaroid.

206
00:13:15.526 --> 00:13:16.694
Do you know these people?

207
00:13:18.237 --> 00:13:20.031
Tommy Shuster. Erica...

208
00:13:20.657 --> 00:13:23.368
Charles. I think. I shot
Tommy a few times for baseball.

209
00:13:24.827 --> 00:13:26.955
- So they go here?
- They did.

210
00:13:27.580 --> 00:13:29.374
They were seniors when we were freshmen.

211
00:13:32.043 --> 00:13:33.918
Do you think he knew Scott Reed?

212
00:13:33.920 --> 00:13:36.631
Don't all those troglodytes
know each other? Why do you care?

213
00:13:39.968 --> 00:13:41.094
I'm not sure I do.

214
00:13:45.181 --> 00:13:47.431
Only have a second. coach.
I got a class waiting.

215
00:13:47.433 --> 00:13:48.349
What's up?

216
00:13:48.351 --> 00:13:49.388
Well. I understand

217
00:13:49.389 --> 00:13:52.689
you had a little chat with
one of my players yesterday.

218
00:13:53.605 --> 00:13:56.314
I'd appreciate it if you'd
come see me first next time.

219
00:13:56.317 --> 00:13:58.776
Okay. well. it's my job to
have a chat with students.

220
00:13:58.778 --> 00:13:59.734
I can't be coming to you

221
00:13:59.735 --> 00:14:01.904
every time one of them
happens to play baseball.

222
00:14:01.906 --> 00:14:02.907
No. sure. sure.

223
00:14:03.992 --> 00:14:06.867
Look. I'm glad we're
working on awareness.

224
00:14:06.869 --> 00:14:09.179
and educating these kids about consent.

225
00:14:09.180 --> 00:14:11.297
and everything you're doing. It's great.

226
00:14:11.300 --> 00:14:13.209
I'm just looking for a little teamwork.

227
00:14:14.056 --> 00:14:15.758
I give the right speeches.

228
00:14:15.761 --> 00:14:19.046
give me a heads up if you've got
a concern about one of my guys.

229
00:14:19.048 --> 00:14:23.594
Okay. I got a concern about
all your guys. Heads up.

230
00:14:25.013 --> 00:14:29.140
You know what. I'm sick of
athletes always being the targets.

231
00:14:29.142 --> 00:14:32.226
Coach. Athletes have the run
of this school. and you know it.

232
00:14:32.228 --> 00:14:34.228
I just don't want them to run kids over.

233
00:14:34.230 --> 00:14:36.774
You want teamwork? Check
your boys. so I don't have to.

234
00:14:40.320 --> 00:14:44.488
We've been talking about how
do you control your impulses.

235
00:14:44.490 --> 00:14:45.814
Today we're going to do an exercise

236
00:14:45.815 --> 00:14:48.619
that will help you think before you act.

237
00:14:49.287 --> 00:14:52.663
Because you're gonna do the
thinking for someone else.

238
00:14:52.665 --> 00:14:55.833
You're gonna be someone
else's eyes and their ears.

239
00:14:55.835 --> 00:14:57.793
and guide them around the room.

240
00:14:57.795 --> 00:15:01.424
- Or out of a window.
- Maybe. Cyrus.

241
00:15:01.427 --> 00:15:04.295
But you'll be switching
blindfolds halfway through.

242
00:15:04.298 --> 00:15:06.599
so don't do anything you
don't want done to you.

243
00:15:07.709 --> 00:15:09.248
Okay?

244
00:15:09.251 --> 00:15:11.498
That means find a partner.

245
00:15:12.310 --> 00:15:13.561
Or I'll find one for you.

246
00:15:14.687 --> 00:15:17.523
You'd think they'd run these
class names by a focus group first.

247
00:15:19.025 --> 00:15:21.694
"Ass Class." You're
a pretty good artist.

248
00:15:24.989 --> 00:15:26.991
Kind words from the master photographer.

249
00:15:33.122 --> 00:15:34.372
That was you. right?

250
00:15:35.208 --> 00:15:37.583
You won that photo contest
with that night vision picture

