00:45:46.183 --> 00:45:49.935
Um... should we... can we be excused?

745
00:45:49.937 --> 00:45:52.313
What's gotten into you?
We're in the middle of dinner.

746
00:45:52.315 --> 00:45:54.690
- Nothing. I'm just full.
- Yeah.

747
00:45:54.692 --> 00:45:58.193
This pasta is filling.
Yeah. it was so good. though.

748
00:45:58.195 --> 00:46:00.946
- So good.
- So thank you. guys. Appreciate it.

749
00:46:00.948 --> 00:46:03.242
- Yeah. Thank you.
- Thanks for dinner. guys.

750
00:46:05.536 --> 00:46:07.163
- Bye.
- You guys are the best. Thanks.

751
00:46:11.250 --> 00:46:12.460
Jesus. what is your...?

752
00:46:14.625 --> 00:46:15.796
Holy shit.

753
00:46:31.062 --> 00:46:32.796
Don't forget to breathe.

754
00:46:32.799 --> 00:46:35.015
- I am breathing.
- You're not. so much.

755
00:46:41.614 --> 00:46:42.988
Wow.

756
00:46:42.990 --> 00:46:46.617
That's some hard hits today.
You got something on your mind?

757
00:46:46.619 --> 00:46:49.872
Nah. I don't. I just need you...

758
00:46:51.248 --> 00:46:54.416
to sign this form for
my probation officer.

759
00:46:54.418 --> 00:46:55.544
Right on.

760
00:46:56.337 --> 00:46:58.756
Six more sessions left. Not bad.

761
00:46:59.382 --> 00:47:02.508
Think your anger's been adequately
managed in our time together?

762
00:47:02.510 --> 00:47:04.470
Huh. I'll let you know.

763
00:47:06.055 --> 00:47:08.641
We gotta get in the ring
before you're done. You and me.

764
00:47:09.308 --> 00:47:13.104
Uh... I don't think so. But thank you.

765
00:47:16.107 --> 00:47:19.402
She washes one dress and
it sets me back five months.

766
00:47:20.027 --> 00:47:22.989
I swear. I was ready to kick
her out right then and there.

767
00:47:26.283 --> 00:47:28.510
But I think she might be a friend.

768
00:47:28.511 --> 00:47:31.244
and I don't have many
of those right now.

769
00:47:33.708 --> 00:47:36.085
- Present company excluded.
- No. I get it.

770
00:47:36.853 --> 00:47:38.544
Friends who aren't in high school.

771
00:47:42.343 --> 00:47:43.633
You know. Andy...

772
00:47:45.052 --> 00:47:46.187
Andy used to tell me.

773
00:47:46.188 --> 00:47:48.178
when I'd listen to the
tapes for the umpteenth time.

774
00:47:48.180 --> 00:47:49.906
and I would call you with new questions.

775
00:47:49.907 --> 00:47:52.562
he would say how inappropriate it was

776
00:47:52.565 --> 00:47:54.559
that I was spending time with you.

777
00:47:54.562 --> 00:47:57.773
Really? You didn't tell him
that I don't play for your team?

778
00:47:59.191 --> 00:48:01.233
What happened to that
boyfriend of yours?

779
00:48:01.235 --> 00:48:04.030
The handsome guy? I haven't
seen him around in weeks.

780
00:48:05.448 --> 00:48:07.158
- Brad.
- Brad.

781
00:48:09.952 --> 00:48:11.065
Yeah. we broke up.

782
00:48:12.371 --> 00:48:14.510
Oh. That's too bad.

783
00:48:16.250 --> 00:48:18.542
- He was pretty.
- Yeah.

784
00:48:18.544 --> 00:48:20.713
He didn't talk much.
but he was very pretty.

785
00:48:22.383 --> 00:48:23.571
What happened?

786
00:48:24.704 --> 00:48:26.052
Um...

787
00:48:27.136 --> 00:48:29.263
He didn't want to date a kid anymore.

788
00:48:31.307 --> 00:48:35.017
Wanted bigger things. He was
tired of the high school bullshit.

789
00:48:35.019 --> 00:48:37.686
Here I am. bringing you more
high school bullshit. huh?

790
00:48:37.688 --> 00:48:41.442
No. never. I'm here for you. always.

791
00:48:46.322 --> 00:48:48.741
God. I sit in that courtroom. Tony.

792
00:48:51.285 --> 00:48:53.371
and I feel like I
never knew my daughter.

793
00:48:55.790 --> 00:49:01.128
She kept all these... secrets.
Why did she have so many secrets?

794
00:49:03.547 --> 00:49:04.632
I think. uh...

795
00:49:06.717 --> 00:49:09.097
I think. sometimes. we
aren't keeping secrets

796
00:49:09.098 --> 00:49:10.471
to hide from other people.

797
00:49:12.223 --> 00:49:16.266
I think. sometimes. we're keeping
them to protect those people.

798
00:49:21.816 --> 00:49:23.376
- What's wrong?
- Nothing.

799
00:49:27.488 --> 00:49:30.322
- Okay. just stop.
- Wait. I...

800
00:49:30.324 --> 00:49:31.575
Stop. Just...

801
00:49:39.416 --> 00:49:44.711
- Are you ashamed of me?
- What? Skye. no. I...

802
00:49:44.713 --> 00:49:47.174
Then what the fuck is
going on here. Clay?

803
00:49:48.008 --> 00:49:51.220
I mean. why didn't your
parents know about me?

804
00:49:52.138 --> 00:49:55.114
Because they're my parents. They meddle.

805
00:49:55.115 --> 00:49:57.782
Honestly. it has nothing to do with you.

806
00:49:57.785 --> 00:49:59.575
- Really?
- Yeah.

807
00:49:59.578 --> 00:50:02.813
It doesn't have to do
with the way I look?

808
00:50:02.815 --> 00:50:06.150
Or that I have. like.
tattoos and piercings

809
00:50:06.152 --> 00:50:07.901
and. like. cuts all over?

810
00:50:07.903 --> 00:50:10.904
Jesus. Skye. no. I don't
care about that stuff.

811
00:50:10.906 --> 00:50:12.507
You know that.

812
00:50:12.510 --> 00:50:17.037
- You don't care. Of course.
- Wait...

813
00:50:18.359 --> 00:50:21.081
Skye. hang on. Let's just...

814
00:50:21.083 --> 00:50:22.624
That's not what I meant. okay?

815
00:50:22.626 --> 00:50:26.837
What I mean is. I like the
way you look. I like you.

816
00:50:26.840 --> 00:50:30.215
Really? Because your body
is kinda saying the opposite.

817
00:50:30.218 --> 00:50:32.381
Maybe my head's still scrambled

818
00:50:32.384 --> 00:50:34.553
from you trying to jerk me
off in front of my parents.

819
00:50:34.555 --> 00:50:36.138
Well. I'm sorry!

820
00:50:36.140 --> 00:50:39.516
I'm sorry for trying to
be fucking spontaneous!

821
00:50:39.518 --> 00:50:42.843
You could've talked to me. you didn't
have to just show up at my house.

822
00:50:42.846 --> 00:50:44.200
It was weird!

823
00:50:44.203 --> 00:50:45.165
I'll tell you what's weird:

824
00:50:45.166 --> 00:50:48.166
you still being in love
with a fucking dead girl.

825
00:50:50.946 --> 00:50:52.029
Don't...

826
00:50:52.031 --> 00:50:55.659
- Don't say that. please. That's not true.
- Really?

827
00:50:56.619 --> 00:50:58.636
You freaked out at our spot last night

828
00:50:58.637 --> 00:51:00.329
the day that her case is going to trial.

829
00:51:00.331 --> 00:51:02.098
Then you freaked out at lunch today

830
00:51:02.099 --> 00:51:04.166
because I brought up you going to court.

831
00:51:04.168 --> 00:51:08.420
It's like. wherever we go. she's there!

832
00:51:08.422 --> 00:51:09.590
No. That's not...

833
00:51:10.883 --> 00:51:12.132
that's insane.

834
00:51:12.134 --> 00:51:13.550
Is it?

835
00:51:13.552 --> 00:51:17.741
It's all about Hannah.
Clay. and it always will be.

836
00:51:17.744 --> 00:51:20.421
How am I supposed to compete with that?

837
00:51:20.424 --> 00:51:23.476
She's perfect. And she's dead.

838
00:51:23.479 --> 00:51:27.107
- Really. Skye. Can we sit and talk?
- I don't wanna fucking sit down!

839
00:51:28.901 --> 00:51:31.487
Tell me I'm wrong. Tell me you love me.

840
00:51:32.988 --> 00:51:35.572
Tell me you're over her. then.

841
00:51:35.574 --> 00:51:38.905
I... I love you. I...

842
00:51:38.908 --> 00:51:40.038
And?

843
00:51:42.539 --> 00:51:44.792
And you're over me. Clay.
it's okay. just say it.

844
00:51:50.506 --> 00:51:52.216
- Clay?
- I can't!

845
00:51:56.136 --> 00:51:59.306
I'm sorry. but I can't say that.

846
00:52:01.476 --> 00:52:05.227
You have been lying to me.

847
00:52:05.229 --> 00:52:07.145
you fucking liar!

848
00:52:07.147 --> 00:52:10.482
Skye! Skye! Shit.

849
00:52:10.484 --> 00:52:11.777
Skye!

850
00:52:12.861 --> 00:52:13.988
Skye.

851
00:52:21.954 --> 00:52:23.954
Skye.

852
00:52:27.538 --> 00:52:28.765
Fuck.

853
00:52:31.713 --> 00:52:35.381
- What are you gonna do?
- I'm gonna go after her.

854
00:52:35.384 --> 00:52:39.511
- You sure that's a good idea?
- No. I think it's a terrible idea.

855
00:52:39.513 --> 00:52:42.858
But a worse idea is staying here
and discussing it all with you. so...

856
00:52:43.642 --> 00:52:46.476
You think that's what she
wants. for you to chase her?

857
00:52:46.478 --> 00:52:49.648
Are you serious right now?
Are you fucking serious?

858
00:52:51.275 --> 00:52:53.233
"Part of me was saying. 'Don't go.'"

859
00:52:53.235 --> 00:52:56.737
Remember that. Hannah?
Your words. My tape.

860
00:52:56.739 --> 00:52:59.239
- "Part of me was saying. 'Don't go.'"
- I remember.

861
00:52:59.241 --> 00:53:01.368
Well. there you go.

862
00:53:02.703 --> 00:53:04.121
She's not me. Clay.

863
00:53:05.581 --> 00:53:06.877
No.

864
00:53:06.880 --> 00:53:08.112
No one is.

865
00:53:10.377 --> 00:53:14.698
I think it projects strength
and confidence. don't you?

866
00:53:16.717 --> 00:53:18.635
Maybe we can pull your
hair back a little?

867
00:53:19.762 --> 00:53:21.465
Something like this?

868
00:53:21.468 --> 00:53:24.099
Sure. Mom. Whatever you think.

869
00:53:28.270 --> 00:53:30.147
Want to sleep
in your own bed tonight?

870
00:53:31.023 --> 00:53:33.442
- You must be getting tired of our floor.
- No.

871
00:53:34.838 --> 00:53:36.362
No. I'm not.

872
00:53:38.573 --> 00:53:39.782
Okay.

873
00:53:42.493 --> 00:53:45.579
Or fear of the truth
can keep you trapped in your secrets.

874
00:53:46.580 --> 00:53:47.930
In discovery.

875
00:53:47.931 --> 00:53:51.998
the plaintiffs found that your
date book was missing a page.

876
00:53:52.001 --> 00:53:54.169
which seems to be the page

877
00:53:54.171 --> 00:53:56.757
from the last date of
your meeting with Hannah.

878
00:53:58.133 --> 00:54:00.133
- Hmm.
- I'm not gonna ask you

879
00:54:00.135 --> 00:54:02.971
why that page is missing. Not
now. not in court. But they will.

880
00:54:05.474 --> 00:54:09.810
Well. I heard you made Courtney
Crimsen come out on the stand today.

881
00:54:09.812 --> 00:54:12.646
That's... that's messed up.

882
00:54:12.648 --> 00:54:14.274
I didn't make her do anything.

883
00:54:16.151 --> 00:54:18.153
I just asked the questions I had to ask.

884
00:54:18.862 --> 00:54:23.158
They're kids. They're children.

885
00:54:24.535 --> 00:54:25.911
They knew what they were doing.

886
00:54:27.566 --> 00:54:28.847
Did you?

887
00:54:39.508 --> 00:54:41.677
And someone
who's keeping a secret...

888
00:54:44.972 --> 00:54:48.475
who's desperate to keep that secret.
and desperate to stay hidden...

889
00:54:52.354 --> 00:54:54.022
can hurt everyone around them.

890
00:55:07.202 --> 00:55:10.620
There will always come a time when
we're forced to face the thing

891
00:55:10.622 --> 00:55:11.913
we're most afraid of.

892
00:55:11.915 --> 00:55:13.167
No. no. no. No.

893
00:55:15.085 --> 00:55:16.209
Skye!

894
00:55:16.211 --> 00:55:19.379
Skye! Wait. Mrs. Miller! What is she...

895
00:55:19.381 --> 00:55:22.257
- What happened?
- Nothing that hasn't happened before.

896
00:55:22.259 --> 00:55:25.493
- I didn't mean to upset her.
- She's not upset. She's ill.

897
00:55:25.496 --> 00:55:27.556
Please. just... just go home.

898
00:55:46.533 --> 00:55:50.496
You really do have a thing
for complicated girls.

899
